[2072|2220] 18:02:51.255 I/NARR-STATE: narrationState → Speaking(segment=NarrationSegment(id=poi_narration_1094800867251484, text=The Phillips Library, part of the Peabody Essex Museum, traces its origins back to 1801 and has long been a vital resource for maritime and regional history. Formed in 1992 by the merger of two historic libraries—the Phillips Library of the Essex Institute and the Stephen Phillips Library of the Peabody Museum of Salem—it now houses an extensive collection of manuscripts, books, maps, and ships’ logbooks. The Phillips Library continues to support research and inspire discovery for both the local community and a global audience., type=HINT, poiName=Phillips Library, voiceId=en-us-x-tpd-local, kind=POI, category=null, refId=poi_narration, isReplay=false)) (autoPlay=true, queueSize=0)
