[3957|2220] 18:08:30.488 I/NARR-STATE: narrationState → Speaking(segment=NarrationSegment(id=poi_narration_1095139783978965, text=Located at 2 Brown Street, the Roger Conant Statue honors a pivotal figure in Salem’s history. Conant arrived in 1626 with the initial settlers of Naumkeag (later Salem) and served as their governor for several years. He is considered one of the founders of the Massachusetts Bay Colony and a vital link to the city’s earliest colonial roots. The statue serves as a reminder of Salem’s beginnings and Conant’s leadership in establishing a permanent settlement., type=HINT, poiName=Roger Conant Statue, voiceId=en-us-x-tpd-local, kind=POI, category=null, refId=poi_narration, isReplay=false)) (autoPlay=true, queueSize=0)
